Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Running Mates and Carpet Baggers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00szs4n
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 11 Aug 2000
Alistair Cooke explains the origins of the American political phrases "carpet bagger" and "running mate" as well as the role of the vice president.